				posted 2004-12-11 05:10&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;
				<A href="edit.php?board=sug&id=1707"><IMG alt="Edit/Delete Message" src="http://www.archspace.org/image/forum/edit.gif" border=0></A> 
			    <A href="reply.php?board=sug&id=1579"><IMG alt="Reply w/Quote" src="http://www.archspace.org/image/forum/quote.gif" border=0></A>
			    <HR color=#000000 SIZE=-1>
			  	About the smaller ships outmaneuvering a large one, yes that's a possibility, but it would depend on how strategically sound the gunmounting of the larger ships is. If you have a mile-long ship with 200 guns on the very front, the little ships could simply zoom about to its side, and being that it's a massive ship, it'd not be able to turn and defeat them.<br />
Another factor, however, is the rotation of the weapons were they to be placed at the front: They could simply turn and fire off any ships that would be around the midsection.<br />
But, the way I see it, a large ship has its guns mounted correctly, and not all in one glob on the front, meaning that if a little ship were to be able to get to its side, it'd still have to face the fury. Lets think realistically, a gunboat wouldn't be able to outmaneuver a laser, they're instant, nor would it be able to speed from a nuclear explosion, nor would their armor (and hull) be sturdy enough to withhold the force of a homing black hole, etc. Small ships just aren't as good, or versatile, logically, or in this system.<br />
Try to make it apply to the 2D battles we have now. <br />
<br />
As for a ship bay existing on a dreadnaught, or whatever other large, carrier-type ship, I already imagine the weapons, with their startling numbers, to be like mounted ships. And if you can make a carrier-class, you probably have the largest, most efficient weapons anyway. What do you need smaller, less damage-resistent, less-firepowered, less-efficient ships for? It's already been proven to me that 20 gunners fleets stand absolutely no chance against a fleet of battleships, so the numbers would still logically be proportioned like that, meaning little ships are eventually useless.			   <P align=right></P>
			</TD>
