			  	This has probably been suggested before too, but here goes.<br />
<br />
I'm new to the game, it's really cool.  I like the design aspect and I'm eager to get my research finished (which is the most important aspect).  The things I see are<br />
<br />
1.)  What to do when the research is over <br />
2.)  Why bother with small ships once I have an industrial base<br />
<br />
As for the research being done, I know there is no benefit for continuing on, and that's a good thing<br />
<br />
As for the small ships....it seems ppl suggest carriers to increase their relevance.  What about tweaking the commanders so that they can command more smaller ships?  For example, a commander who can deal with 40 dooms could handle X*40 gunboats.  This would increase the relevance of smaller ships by allowing more of them into battle (but they would still die quickly).  Does this make alot of logical sense, not really, but we are lobbing black holes and novarization torps at each other.<br />
<br />
Anyway, just a noobish .02 cents on the issue.<br />
